description: Gautam Gambhir and MS Dhoni were seen in cheerful conversation together at a wedding. The event became a reunion for Indian cricketers. Rohit Sharma and Harbhajan Singh also attended. Many other cricketers were present at the function. Bollywood stars like Kriti Sanon and Suniel Shetty also joined the celebration. The Dhoni-Gambhir picture became viral  on social media as well.
title: In pictures: MS Dhoni, Gautam Gambhir, Rohit Sharma, Suniel Shetty clicked at wedding

author: YASH SHARMA
description: Lamborghini unveiled the Fenomeno at Monterey Car Week 2025, a limited-run model celebrating Centro Stile's 20th anniversary. CEO Stephan Winkelmann announced the production of 29 units, priced between 3 and 3.5 million euros. The Fenomeno boasts a 1,064 hp hybrid powertrain, achieving 0-100 kmph in 2.4 seconds and a top speed exceeding 350 kmph.
title: Lamborghini debuts Fenomeno; Winkelmann explains why V12 isn’t done yet

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Security forces in Manipur arrested five militants, including three women from the KCP (Taibanganba), in Thoubal and Imphal East districts. Separately, a PREPAK (PRO) cadre was apprehended. Authorities also seized arms and ammunition during a search operation in Imphal East. The governor highlighted ongoing security efforts to curb extortion and the seizure of over 3,000 firearms in recent months.
title: Manipur: 3 women among 5 militants arrested; arms and ammunition seized

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Mumbai grappled with heavy rainfall on Saturday, leading to waterlogged streets and a tragic landslide in Vikhroli that claimed two lives and injured two others. The IMD has issued a red alert for Mumbai and neighboring districts, forecasting continued intense rainfall. In Himachal Pradesh, the monsoon death toll has reached 257, with widespread disruptions to roads and essential services.
title: Mumbai rains: Heavy downpour floods streets, railway tracks flooded, red alert sounded

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Rubina Irshad Shaikh, a 21-year-old Bangladeshi woman arrested for illegal stay in India, escaped from Mumbai's JJ Hospital. She pushed aside a police constable while receiving treatment for fever and skin ailments after being transferred from Byculla Women’s Jail.
title: Mumbai shocker: Pregnant Bangladeshi prisoner escapes from JJ Hospital; search on

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Karsan Ghavri alleges that Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma were compelled to retire prematurely from Test cricket due to internal politics within the BCCI and the selection committee. Ghavri claims that both players desired to continue playing, but were forced out, and Kohli was not even given a farewell.
title: 'Not like they wanted to leave': Ex-India bowler on Kohli, Rohit retirements

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: In Alaska, President Trump and President Putin engaged in over two and a half hours of discussions primarily focused on the Russia-Ukraine war. Putin faced pointed questions from reporters about civilian casualties and trust. Following the talks, both leaders expressed optimism about a potential path to peace in Ukraine, though specifics of their agreement remained undisclosed.
title: 'Will you stop killing civilians?': How reporters put Putin on the spot with questions in Alaska; watch

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Nazem Kadri expressed disappointment at not being invited to Hockey Canada's Olympic orientation camp, despite a strong recent performance. He highlighted his impressive stats, including a 35-goal season, and emphasized his winning experience. Kadri also addressed trade rumors linking him to Toronto, while reaffirming his commitment to earning an Olympic roster spot through continued production.
title: “I Deserve a Chance”: Nazem Kadri fires back after Hockey Canada camp snub

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A devastating cloudburst in Jammu and Kashmir's Kishtwar district has claimed the lives of at least 60 people, with over 100 injured. Rescue operations are underway, involving multiple agencies and local volunteers, as authorities work to identify victims and locate the missing. The disaster struck near the Machail Mata shrine, destroying infrastructure and prompting the suspension of the annual pilgrimage.
title: Kishtwar cloudburst: 60 dead, 100 injured, several trapped; rescue ops continue for 3rd day

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Following his meeting with Vladimir Putin in Alaska, US President Donald Trump mentioned potentially imposing tariffs on countries purchasing Russian oil in the coming weeks. While no agreements were signed during the three-hour closed-door meeting, both leaders expressed cautious optimism regarding US-Russia relations and the conflict in Ukraine.
title: ‘Maybe in 2-3 weeks’: What Trump said on tariffs over Russian oil after meeting Putin

author: RICHA PINTO
description: In the early hours of Saturday, a landslide in Mumbai's Vikhroli area claimed the lives of two individuals, Shalu Mishra, 19, and Suresh Mishra, 50. The incident occurred when a hut in Jankalyan Society, Varsha Nagar, was struck by falling soil and stones. Two other occupants, Aarti Mishra, 45, and Ruturaj Mishra, 20, were injured and are currently receiving treatment.
title: Mumbai rains: Landslide in Vikhroli kills 2; IMD issues red alert for city

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman has completely abandoned Google Search, saying he "legitimately cannot tell you the last time I did a Google search" during an explosive dinner interview with tech reporters. The admission comes as ChatGPT reaches 700 million weekly users and threatens to topple Google's two-decade dominance of the $175 billion search market, with Altman himself serving as the most high-profile convert to AI-powered search alternatives.
title: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman: I don't use Google anymore, I cannot tell you ...

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Show of force by US: B-2 bomber thundered across skies over Putin’s head in Alaska; watch

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Gail Lane, a 75-year-old Canadian, experienced blindness for ten years. An autoimmune disorder damaged her corneas. She regained her sight through osteo-odonto-keratoprosthesis. This rare surgery uses a patient's tooth as a new cornea. Doctors implanted her tooth in her cheek. Later, they placed it in her eye with a lens. Gail can now see faces and colors.
title: Woman blind for a decade undergoes rare 'tooth in the eye' surgery and regains vision

author: ADVITYA BAHL
description: A Noida couple and their daughter were held captive in an Uber cab when the driver, Nasim, attempted to evade a police check. Ignoring their pleas, Nasim sped away, colliding with another car during the chase. He was later apprehended, and Uber has removed his access to their platform after the family was released on Sector 66 road.
title: Noida horror ride: Family held ‘hostage’ in cab as driver tries to escape cops; arrested

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Despite warm gestures and ceremonial honors, the summit between Trump and Putin in Alaska yielded no concrete agreements, though both leaders expressed optimism and hinted at future contact. Putin's visit marked a return to the global stage after years of isolation, while Trump faced criticism for legitimizing a leader accused of war crimes.
title: Alaska summit: ‘Productive’ talks but 'no deal' on Ukraine - 10 takeaways from Trump-Putin meet

author: ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Rajinikanth's 'Coolie', directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj, has taken the box office by storm, earning Rs 118.5 crore net in India within three days. The film, featuring a star-studded cast including Akkineni Nagarjuna and Aamir Khan, has seen houseful shows across the country. Early estimates suggest 'Coolie' could surpass Rs 150 crore during its opening week, driven by strong audience reception and an extended holiday weekend.
title: ‘Coolie’ box office collections day 3: Rajinikanth's film strikes gold; storms past Rs 118.5

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: In Patna's Indrapuri area, tragedy struck as two children, a girl aged around nine and a boy about five, were discovered deceased inside a parked car on Friday evening. Police responded to a 112 call and found one child alive, but the child later died in hospital.
title: Patna horror: 2 children found dead inside parked car in Indrapuri; probe on

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A recent UK Biobank study involving over 36,000 participants with hypertension reveals that exceeding 3,000 daily steps significantly reduces the risk of heart problems. Each additional 1,000 steps, up to 10,000, further lowers risks of heart events, stroke, and heart failure, with benefits extending to those without high blood pressure.
title: Walking for heart health: How many step counts protect your heart? (and why you don’t need 10,000)

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: A 26-million-year-old whale skull, belonging to the newly identified Janjucetus dullardi, has been unearthed at Jan Juc Beach in Australia. This Oligocene-era predator, unlike modern baleen whales, possessed sharp teeth and large eyes, indicating an active hunting lifestyle. The remarkably preserved fossil offers crucial insights into whale evolution, particularly the transition from toothed predators to filter feeders.
title: Whale skull fossil found: A 26-million-year-old skull; sheds light on ancient marine life

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: SmackDown witnessed Sami Zayn aligning with Jimmy Uso and Jacob Fatu against The MFTs, securing a victory in the main event. Alexa Bliss triumphed over Piper Niven, while Melo Don’t Miz defeated Fraxiom. Drew McIntyre addressed his attack on Cody Rhodes, and the Street Profits overcame #DIY. The episode set the stage for future rivalries and matches, including MCMG vs.
title: WWE SmackDown: Alexa Bliss stuns Piper Niven; Street Profits extend streak and more

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Jacksonville Jaguars' rookie Travis Hunter's recent marriage to Leanna Lenee is under scrutiny. Lenee once revealed that Hunter initially contacted her while he was in another relationship, which she rejected. Despite defending their relationship against accusations of ulterior motives, divorce rumors are now circulating, adding to the couple's challenges.
title: Leanna Lenee: Jaguars rookie Travis Hunter slid into my DMs while dating

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Krishna Janmashtami, celebrating Lord Krishna's birth, falls on August 15 and 16 in 2025. It commemorates Krishna's birth in Mathura over 5,000 years ago, symbolizing hope and righteousness. Celebrations include fasting, decorating idols, and reenactments of Krishna's life, with Dahi Handi being a popular tradition. The Bhagavad Gita's teachings are also remembered during this auspicious time.
title: Happy Krishna Janmashtami 2025: Best Janmashtami wishes, messages, quotes to share

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Following a lengthy meeting with Vladimir Putin, Donald Trump asserted that resolving the Ukraine conflict hinges on Volodymyr Zelenskyy's willingness to negotiate. Trump suggested that European nations should also play a role and expressed his availability to participate in future discussions between Zelenskyy and Putin, indicating a high likelihood of reaching an agreement.
title: 'Make a deal': Trump’s blunt message to Zelenskyy after meeting Putin

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Pakistan is grappling with devastating flash floods. Heavy rains have caused widespread destruction. At least 243 people have died, with many still missing. Buner district is the worst affected. Rescue efforts are underway to reach stranded families. A helicopter carrying relief supplies crashed. Climate change is believed to be a contributing factor.
title: Pakistan floods kill 243: Buner worst hit with 157 deaths; relief helicopter crashes

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: PM Narendra Modi paid tribute to Atal Bihari Vajpayee on his death anniversary. He acknowledged Vajpayee's service to India. PM Modi said his contributions continued to inspire the nation.Several Union ministers visited Sadaiv Atal, Vajpayee’s memorial in Delhi. Kiren Rijiju, Gajendra Singh Shekhawat, Sanjay Jha, and Rekha Gupta were present. Vajpayee, the first BJP prime minister, passed away in 2018.
title: Vajpayee’s death anniversary: PM pays tribute; calls him guiding force for self-reliant India

author: TNN
description: The Centre has proposed a GST 2.0 blueprint, aiming for simpler taxation with two main slabs of 5% and 18%. This revamp seeks to eliminate the 12% and 28% slabs, end compensation cess, and tax sin goods at 40%.
title: GST 2.0: 12% & 28% slabs set to go; sin goods face 40% levy

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Irfan Pathan revealed that Hardik Pandya, not Virat Kohli or Rohit Sharma, raised concerns about his on-air criticism during the Australia Test series in December 2024, leading to his removal from the IPL 2025 broadcast team.
title: Not Virat or Rohit - Irfan Pathan names the player who wanted him out of IPL commentary

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Ayan Mukerji's 'WAR 2,' starring Hrithik Roshan, Jr NTR, and Kiara Advani, had a strong opening, boosted significantly by its Telugu version. Despite mixed reviews, the film experienced substantial growth on Independence Day, particularly in its Hindi version, which saw a 50% jump. The movie crossed ₹100 crore in two days, although Telugu collections dipped slightly on the second day.
title: 'War 2' box office collection day 2: Hrithik Roshan, Jr NTR starrer crosses Rs 100 crore

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Devotees are preparing to celebrate the 5252nd birth anniversary of Lord Krishna on Janmashtami, observed on August 15th and 16th, 2025. The festival, also known as Gokulashtami, marks the birth of Lord Krishna, the eighth incarnation of Lord Vishnu, revered for vanquishing injustice. Celebrations include fasting until midnight and worshipping Lord Krishna's idol.
title: 75+ Happy Krishna Janmashtami wishes, messages, greetings and quotes for 2025

author: TNN
description: NHAI has introduced an annual toll pass for FASTag users, witnessing approximately 1.4 lakh purchases and transactions on the first day. The pass, priced at Rs 3,000, is valid for a year or 200 toll plaza crossings for non-commercial vehicles. NHAI has deployed officials and strengthened its helpline to ensure a smooth experience for pass users.
title: FASTag: Annual toll pass rolled out; 1.4 lakh transactions on 1st day

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Mara Teigen, Evander Kane's fiancee, faced a wardrobe crisis in France before Leon Draisaitl's wedding. Her clothes bag went missing upon arrival in Marseille, leaving her with limited options. Teigen found a replacement dress at an outlet mall, but it wasn't her ideal choice. Eventually, she discovered a Zimmerman dress in a boutique, saving the day.
title: Evander Kane’s fiancee Mara Teigen recalls nightmare last minute dress hunt

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway is secretly building a substantial position, estimated at nearly $5 billion, sparking widespread speculation. CNBC prompted AI chatbots like ChatGPT, Google Gemini, and Microsoft Copilot to identify the mystery stock using Berkshire's filings. ChatGPT suggested GE Aerospace, while Microsoft Copilot surprisingly picked Visa.
title: What ChatGPT, Google Gemini and Microsoft Copilot think is 'mystery stock' of Warren Buffet
